SUMMARY:Tryon Spring Storytime\, Nature Walk & Craft
DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Tryon Creek and local author\, illustrator\, and naturalist Audrey Sauble for a special storytime series. Featuring a variety of nature themes and books\, some of which are available to purchase in the Nature Center Store. We will gather near the Nature Center for a story\, activity\, and walk introducing children (and adults) to forest plants and animals. It is best suited for children 3-5 years old\, but all are welcome. $10 (free for members). \nSpring Storytime Themes \n\n\nMarch 6: Owls \n\n\nMarch 13: Banana Slugs \n\n\nApril 17: Trees & Seeds \n\n\nApril 24: Frogs & Amphibians \n\n\nMay 8: Flowers & Pollinators \n\n\nMay 22: Coyotes \n\n\nThis event is free for current Friends of Tryon Creek members (use this express membership link and join today) or $10 for each family for non-members. Use the links above to register. If you are not a current member\, you can use the link above to join and then you will be asked to create an account before registering. If space is available\, registration is also available the day-of at the Nature Center Store. \nEditor’s note: This event is a community submission.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/tryon-spring-storytime-nature-walk-craft/2026-03-13/
LOCATION:Tryon Creek State Natural Area
CATEGORIES:Arts/Crafts,Kids Calendar,Plants & Nature,Storytime
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://pdxparent.com/wp-content/uploads/spring-series.png
END:VEVENT
